  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Optional chaining only runs code at the next step of a property chain if it's defined. We could use this property to prevent running debug code with minimal syntax boilerplate. For example:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nfunction forever() {\r\n  while (true) {}\r\n}\r\nconst logger = {}\r\n\r\nlogger.debug?.(forever())\r\n```  \r\n\r\nA more realistic example would look like\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nlogger.debug?.(\"Some data\", {\r\n  root: expensiveComputation(data)\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd we set logger.debug = undefined if logger level is greater than debug",
